One Villager Killed in Latest Kosovo Violence
BELGRADE , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- Armed men killed an ethnic Albanian villager in the Serbian autonomous province of Kosovo on Friday evening , the Tanjug news agency reported Saturday .
The gunmen , wearing uniforms of the Kosovo Liberation Army , broke into a house in Prekoluk village , killed the father and severely wounded the son .
The killing brought to 16 the toll in Kosovo violence after Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke struck a deal on peaceful settlement of the Kosovo crisis a month ago , the report said .
More than 150 ethnic Albanian villagers in Prekoluk sought police protection following the attack , saying they would have to flee their home without the protection .
